squeak.translation[0].definitions[0].def: to make a short high noise or cry that is not loud
squeak.translation[0].definitions[0].exa: A rat squeaked and ran into the bushes.
squeak.translation[0].definitions[1].def: to say something in a very high voice, especially because you are nervous or excited
squeak.translation[0].definitions[2].def: to succeed, win, or pass a test by a very small amount so that you only just avoid failure
squeak.translation[0].definitions[2].exa: She just squeaked through her math test.
squeak.translation[1].definitions[0].def: a very short high noise or cry
squeak.translation[1].definitions[0].exa: the high-pitched squeak of a bat
